@u_loose wrote:

[quote=“Pk-Xile, post:7, topic:528820”][quote author=Bl3nd link=topic=647573.msg4355546#msg4355546 date=1377476435]

Both are missing bl3nd, When you search through all the cache,client and source the only thing that comes up that its in the client/javafiles

Its trying to find the cache which is in your users folder. So go to your user and from what I see 'Dominic? - go into that folder and then deathlypvpzv5/Data/maps, for the first folder, then add mapConfig.txt in there. Maybe you can just create new file, then just type in that name and it might work. If the second one is missing do the same, and go into the classpath the cmd is referring to.
[/quote]

Found them, i’ve changed the path but now nothing happens on the cmd & its still stuck at requesting title screen omg -.-

p9k41.png1023×557

OR SOMEONE JUST GIVE ME A GOOD SOURCE JESUS[/quote]

Also in cacdownloader.java make sure the link to your cache is something like
Http://dl.dropbox.com
